#Text=Maria Landini
#Text=Maria Landini
#Text=[ lower-alpha 1 ]

#Text=( c. 1668 – 22 June 1722 ) was an Italian soprano who began her career as a singer at the court of Queen Christina in Rome but was primarily active at the imperial court in Vienna from 1711 until her death .

#Text=She created numerous soprano roles in operas and oratorios by Fux , Caldara , and her second husband , Francesco Bartolomeo Conti and was reputedly the highest paid musician in Vienna at the time . [ 2 ] [ 1 ]
#Text=Life and career
#Text=Landini 's mother , Francesca Portui , was the maid of Queen Christina of Sweden and married to Francesco Landini , the captain of Christina 's guards .
#Text=However , Francesco Landini was not her real father .
#Text=Maria was born from a relationship between her mother and the marquise Orazio Del Monte , Christina 's chamberlain .
#Text=According to 17th-century sources , she was born in Hamburg where Christina 's court periodically sojourned , although the date of her birth has variously been given as 1667 , 1668 , and 1670 .
#Text=Maria spent her entire childhood and youth at the court of Queen Christina where she was trained as a singer and was known by the diminutive " Mariuccia " .
#Text=By the late 1680s there are records of her regularly performing in private musical evenings at Queen Christina 's court in Rome .
#Text=She often sang together with another favourite singer of the queen , Angela Voglia ( known as " La Giorgina " ) . [ 3 ]
#Text=After Queen Christina 's death in 1689 , Landini entered the service of Sophia Charlotte of Hanover in Germany .
#Text=She married an actor named " Chateauneuf " in Hannover in 1695 and sometimes appeared under the name " Landini di Chateauneuf " or its Italian version " Castelnovo " . [ 4 ]
#Text=According to Francesco Conti 's biographer Hermine Williams , Castelnovo was from an aristocratic family and his full name was Mallo di Castelnuovo .
#Text=Their marriage would produce three children : Ferdinando , Francesca , and Caterina .
#Text=Landini was active in the opera houses of Italy from 1698 when she was in the service of the Duke of Mantua .
#Text=Her earliest appearance in Mantua was in 1698 in Bononcini ' s Il Trionfo di Camilla .

#Text=She also appeared in Venice , Genoa , Casale Monferrato , Livorno , Modena , and Bologna before moving to Vienna in 1710 where she became the prima donna of Emperior Charles VI ' s court theatre .
#Text=In 1714 , following the death of her first husband , Landini married Francesco Bartolomeo Conti in Vienna 's Schottenkirche .
#Text=In her will , written in the year prior to her death , she asked to be buried in the Schottenkirche next to her first husband . [ 5 ]
#Text=In 1725 Conti married Anna Maria Lorenzani who had succeeded Landini as the prima donna at the imperial court . [ 5 ]
#Text=Roles created
#Text=Roles created by Maria Landini include :
#Text=Clori in Johann Joseph Fux ' s La decima fatica di Ercole , Habsburg court theatre , Vienna , 1710 [ 6 ]
#Text=Merope in Francesco Gasparini ' s Merope , Teatro San Cassiano , Venice , 26 December 1711 [ 7 ]
#Text=Dafne in Johann Joseph Fux 's Dafne in Lauro , Habsburg court theatre , Vienna , 1714 [ 6 ]
#Text=Euridice in Johann Joseph Fux 's Orfeo ed Euridice , Habsburg court theatre , Vienna , 1715 [ 6 ]
#Text=Angelica in Johann Joseph Fux 's Angelica , vincitrice di Alcina , Habsburg court theatre , Vienna , 1716 [ 6 ]
#Text=Ifigenia in Johann Joseph Fux 's Diana plaeata , Habsburg court theatre , Vienna , 1717 [ 6 ]
#Text=Lucinda in Francesco Bartolomeo Conti 's Don Chisciotte in Sierra Morena , Habsburg court theatre , Vienna , 6 February 1719 [ 8 ]
